<% title = "#{@config.name}" %>
<% content_for(:title, title) %>
<% breadcrumb(title) %>

<h1><%=title%></h1>
<%=render "global_alert"%>
<p>
Openpilot has some compatibility with the <strong><%=@model.name %></strong> and this page serves as a general overview of the model.<br />
To get more specific details on compatibility of a particular trim ensure you check the trim links below to learn more.
</p>

<p>The goal is to always support as many vehicles as possible.</p>

<% if !@make.slack_channel.blank? %>
<p>
To chat about the <%=@config.vehicle_make.name%> <%=@config.vehicle_model.name%> with the community, checkout the <a href="slack://channel?team=comma&id=<%=@make.slack_channel%>">#<%=@make.slack_channel%></a> channel in the <a href="https://slack.comma.ai" target="_blank">Comma Slack</a>.
</p>
<% end %>

<h2>Research and Support</h2>

<p>The first thing we need to know is if the vehicle has Adaptive Cruise Control (ACC) and Lane Keeping Assist (LKA).
<% if @config.vehicle_make_package.present? %>
  <br />On <%=@make.name%> vehicles, this is called the <%=@config.vehicle_make_package.name%> package.</p>
<% end %>
<p>Although most model trims have similar factory hardware, some may differ slightly so ensure you check the trim pages for specifics.</p>
<%# <p>We've found the following trims for this configuration.</p> %>

<h3>Identify your exact trim</h3>
<h4>Standard Trims</h4>

<p>The following trims come standard with the features required for Openpilot to work effectively.</p>
<div class="alert alert-info"><strong style="margin-right:25px;">NOTE</strong> Although they come with these features, it is not guaranteed that Openpilot is 100% compatible. 
If you discover any issues, work with a community member to get your vehicle ported to its reach its full potential.</div>

<ul>
  <% @config.trim_styles.select{|ts| ts.driver_assist_inclusion == "standard"}.each do |trim| %>
  <li>
    <%=link_to vehicles_admin_show_trim_path(config_slug: @config.slug.present? ? @config.slug : @config.id, trim_style_id: trim.id) do %>
      <%=trim.year%> <%=trim.name%>
    <% end %>
  </li>
  <% end %>
</ul>

<%if @config.vehicle_make_package %>
  <h4>Trims w/ <%=@config.vehicle_make_package.name %> Option</h4>

  <p>The following trims do not come standard with the features required for Openpilot to work effectively.</p>
  <p>Review the features that come with these models thoroughly to ensure your vehicle has the right hardware.</p>

  <ul>
    <% @config.trim_styles.select{|ts| ts.driver_assist_inclusion == "option" }.each do |trim| %>
    <li>
      <%=link_to vehicles_admin_show_trim_path(config_slug: @config.slug.present? ? @config.slug : @config.id, trim_style_id: trim.id) do %>
        <%=trim.year%> <%=trim.name%>
      <% end %>
    </li>
    <% end %>
  </ul>

  <h4>Not Supported</h4>

  <p>Unfortunately the following <%=@make.name%> <%@model.name%> trims are not supported.</p>
  <p>They simply lack the hardware necessary for Openpilot to work effectively.</p>

  <ul>
    <% @config.trim_styles.select{|ts| ts.driver_assist_inclusion.blank? }.each do |trim| %>
    <li>
      <%=trim.year%> <%=trim.name%>
    </li>
    <% end %>
  </ul>
<% end %>